@zkKirol 
> I think in our use case this may not be working as
it can _only_ ever work with `this`. to send tokens, a contract has to make the token send part of the account update created by the method - only that way, the send is authorized with a proof. that's an important constraint to keep in mind no matter what your design looks like

when you're calling fetchAccount() you need to pass token ID as 2nd parameter

in your test do:
``` import {TokenId} from 'o1js';
const derivedTokenId = TokenId.derive(contractAddress);
const result = await fetchAccount({
 publicKey: contractAddress,
 tokenId: derivedTokenId, 
});
```
